main event: A local engineer reported a sighting of a disc-shaped object with green and orange lights in San Diego on 9 May 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as tubular shaped, approximately 50 feet long with a 20 feet diameter., The sighting was made by a civilian couple and lasted for 2 minutes., Members of a 'Flying Saucer Sighting Club' were involved in tracking sightings in the area., Other sightings were reported during the same time period, including a green fireball., The object made no sound during the observation.
sighted object: disc-shaped object with green and orange lights
witness description: civilian couple, member of 'Flying Saucer Club'
